title: Metropolitan Statistical Areas, Florida, 2003
name: Metropolitan Statistical Areas, Florida, 2003
description:
This dataset contains the boundaries for metropolitan statistical areas for the State of Florida. The data set contains information on location, identification, and size.
  Content Purpose:  The data provide users with information about the locations, names, and sizes of MSAs primarily for national planning applications. The MA(s) and the central cities within an MA are designated and defined by the federal Office of Management and Budget (OMB), following a set of official standards that are published in a Federal Register Notice. The interagency Federal Executive Committee on Metropolitan Areas developed these standards, with the aim of producing definitions that are as consistent as possible for all MA(s) nationwide.
